Author: THOMSON
Vol / Page: 101
Edition:
Quote: Having small interest in different types of lures, flies and whatnots, I asked the field officer what kind of bait he caught it on, the reply being a `nickel spinner'! ... Cliff told me that the `nickel spinner' was a .303 rifle bullet. <i> Ibid.</i> 169 The remainder of the day seemed to drag slowly, and we took a stroll up the river to try our luck with a spot of fishing with a nickel spinner.
