Date: 0/0/1980
Source: Personal Kiwi-Yankee Dictionary, A
Author: LELAND
Vol / Page: 70
Edition:
Quote: nickel spinner: Another horror story for the devoted fisherman. A BULLET (not necessarily nickel plated) fired at a trout (or any other fish). This almost always misses but it stuns the fish which then float to the surface to be gathered in.
